        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29246",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Exactly the same for me today.\nRalph, I will correct this like I already did for LOB_AS_STRING.\nBut in my idea, default state is activation of OCI_RETURN_NULLS and deactivation if needed.\nWhat do you think about it?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-03T01:18:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-03T01:19:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29311",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harabanar",
                        "name": "harabanar",
                        "displayName": "Helgi Hrafn Halld\u00f3rsson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I got in to the same problem as listed above, but this does not affect version 1.6.0 or 1.6.2\n\nI agree with Mickael Perraud, that OCI_RETURN_NULLS should be set by default and deactivated if needed.\n\nI will still use 1.6.2 until this is fixed :S",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harabanar",
                        "name": "harabanar",
                        "displayName": "Helgi Hrafn Halld\u00f3rsson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-06T05:31:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-06T07:07:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29323",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in SVN 14241 and merge back to 1.7 branch in SVN 14242\n\nWith correction of ZF-5146, I exchanged oci_fetch_row and oci_fetch_assoc with oci_fetch_array. The normal behaviour of oci_fetch_row and oci_fecth_assoc is to return null for empty field but not for oci_fetch_array. This behaviour wasn't cover by unit test. This is now ok with SVN 14241.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-07T08:43:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-08T04:23:15.000+0000"
                }
            ]
